However, if you want to remove the username and password from the URL string without parsing it, you can use a regular expression:

```javascript
function stripCredentialsFromUrl(url) {
    return url.replace(/^https?:\/\/([^:]+):([^:]+)(.*)$/, '$1$3');
}

// Example usage:
const url = 'https://username:password@example.com/path';
console.log(stripCredentialsFromUrl(url));
```

This regular expression works by matching the entire URL string and capturing the protocol, username, password, and the rest of the URL. It then replaces the matched string with the protocol and the rest of the URL, effectively removing the username and password.

