```javascript
const stars = document.querySelectorAll('.star');

stars.forEach((star, index) => {
  star.addEventListener('click', () => {
    console.log(index);
  });
});
```

2. **Use a named function**: Similar to the closure solution, you can use a named function to capture the index.

```javascript
const stars = document.querySelectorAll('.star');

